The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Borde profile

The following is a brief profile of former captain Chandu Borde, who was appointed as manager on Tuesday for Team Indias upcoming tours of Ireland and England. 

 Born: Poona

 (now Pune) on 21 July, 1934 

 Current age: 72 years, 326 days 

 Role: Allrounder (right hand middle-order batsman and right arm leg-break bowler) 

 Tests: 55 (1958-59 to 1969-70) 

 Runs: 3061 35.59 

 Wickets: 52 46.48 

 Test 100s: 5 (Best: 177* vs Pak, Madras, 1960-61) 

 5-wkt Test hauls: 1 (5/88 vs England, Madras, 1963-64) 

 Test catches: 37 

 First-class career (1952-53 to 1972-73): 251 matches; 12,805 runs 40.91; 100s-30; 331 wkts 27.32 

 Was manager during Indias tour of Pakistan in 1989-90. This series marked Sachin Tendulkars international debut. Krishnamachari Srikkanth was the captain. 

 Member of the selection committee: 1982-83, 1983-84. 

 Chairman of selectors: 1984-85, 1985-86, 1999-00 to 2001-2002. 

 Winner of the Arjuna award: 1966 

 Winner of Padma Bhushan: 2002 

 Winner of BCCI Lifetime achievement award : 2006 

COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON




